## ğŸ¯ Objective
To understand the role of Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) in protecting user privacy, encrypting data, and securing communications. This is achieved through practical testing using ProtonVPN on Windows and analyzing traffic with Wireshark.

---

## ğŸ” Scope
This project covers:
- VPN basics and their importance in modern internet usage.
- Encryption mechanisms used in VPNs.
- Privacy protection through IP masking and DNS leak prevention.
- Tunneling protocols and their differences (WireGuard vs OpenVPN).
- Network security enhancements provided by VPNs.

